Two men have been arrested and two illegal firearms confiscated in two separate police operations in Cape Town, Western Cape police said on Saturday. Constables Shane Samuels and Gordon Mowers with one of the confiscated firearms. Photo: SAPS On Friday afternoon, Mitchell s Plain South African Police Service (SAPS) officers acted on information received from the public about an unlicensed firearm and ammunition kept at a residence in Polo Street, Beacon Valley, Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said. Upon arrival on the scene a search was conducted and a 7.65mm pistol and five rounds of ammunition were discovered hidden underneath a bed in one of the bedrooms. A 37-year-old man was arrested. In a separate incident on Saturday morning, Mitchell s Plain police arrested a 32-year-old man for possession of an illegal firearm and ammunition in Eastridge. Officers had received information that a firearm was being kept at a house in Maroela Street. Upon their arrival they searched one of the bedrooms and discovered a Taurus 9mm pistol with eight rounds of ammunition. The members enquired about the firearm and discovered that the owner of the pistol did not have a licence to possess the firearm. Both suspects would appear in the Mitchells Plain Magistrate s Court on Monday on charges of possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition, Rwexana said.